&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Freelance Senior Copywriter with 5-7 years’ experience in pharma advertising, marketing, or marketing communications. You will concept and develop brand campaigns and write copy for a variety of digital marketing tactics for pharma clients. Relevant experience and ability quickly decipher marketing assignments for complex clients is required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities, including but not limited to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop concepts and collaborate with art directors to produce creative campaign and project ideas for various clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create ideas and write copy for digital and print marketing materials, including websites, presentations, brochures, promotional videos, conference and event themes/booths, and brand/product positioning and messaging decks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand and apply brand goals, positioning, and market conditions to the work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Craft message matrices to bring brand positioning to life in a customer-facing copy that highlights the brand’s story and its and key benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a sound knowledge of clients&#39; products, competitors, and target audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present work to internal teams and to clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work with the Strategy and Content team to develop content audits that leads to content strategy recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Incorporate ideas and make revisions in response to the feedback from your supervisors, account team and clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work collaboratively with creative leads, account team and project management to deliver work at a high level&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be responsible for monitoring and follow-through of work on all assigned projects within established timelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be detail-oriented and proof own work to keep quality assurance across projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications and Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5-7 years of related work experience in pharma advertising.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to write skillfully across multiple channels, including print(Sales Brochures, Print Ads, Infographics), online video, and digital (websites, online banners, social media, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong conceptual skills, as demonstrated by your portfolio of work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to dive into complex science and technologies and glean key ideas and information to convey to target audiences that meet the objective&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of and expertise in pharma copy requirements: claims, references, research, and copy that meets the requirements of the FDA and client med/reg/legal review&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An understanding of agency and creative collaboration processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to present and sell an idea to internal teams and clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Microsoft Office suite, Adobe Acrobat, and Google Suite tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports To: &lt;/strong&gt;Associate Creative Director, Copy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;At CG Life, we recognize that attracting the best talent is key to our strategy and success as a company. As a result, we aim for flexibility in structuring competitive compensation offers to ensure we are able to attract the best candidates. As required by law in this state, the estimated hourly range for this position is $85 - $100 USD and represents our good faith estimate as to what our ideal candidates are likely to expect. We tailor our offers within the range based on organizational needs, internal equity, market data, geographic zone, and the selected candidate’s experience, education, industry knowledge, location, technical and communication skills, and other factors that may prove relevant during the selection proces

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Marketing Operations Associate is responsible for building and publishing high-quality, responsive web pages in Adobe Experience Manager using pre-designed components and approved content, under the guidance of senior team members. Success in this role looks like consistently delivering accurate, on-brand pages with a growing attention to detail and a willingness to learn. This is an junior level role focused on developing core production skills while helping translate creative and strategic work into polished, functional digital experiences. Within the agency, this position supports content production, working closely with designers, copywriters, and project teams to bring campaigns and websites to life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities, including but not limited to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate finalized design files and copy documents into fully built, responsive web pages using Adobe Experience Manager (AEM), with support and review from senior team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create, edit, and manage content using existing components and templates within AEM.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure visual and functional consistency with approved brand standards and creative direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Upload and manage assets (images, documents, media) in AEM’s Digital Asset Management (DAM) system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct basic content QA to validate layout, links, formatting, and page behavior across browsers and devices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely the team to meet critical deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications and Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1–3 years of experience managing content in a CMS or similar tool/platform; hands-on Adobe Experience Manager (AEM) experience is a plus but not required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in learning web publishing best practices and digital content lifecycle management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to detail, with a strong sense of layout, hierarchy, and brand consistency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Workfront or similar project management tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to participate in content quality assurance processes and collaborate with QA teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail with the ability to work quickly and efficiently under deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working in a fast-paced, collaborative environment,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in life sciences or other regulated industries is a plus, but not required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic understanding of HTML/CSS is a plus, but not required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Benefits:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are proud to offer a comprehensive benefits package to all of our employees:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Medical, Dental &amp;amp; Vision Insurance.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;We cover a generous portion of employee contributions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;401K plan.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;We invest in present and future you, which is why we offer a generous match and immediate vesting on our plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parental Leave.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Generous paid time off for parents to bond with their newest addition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Professional Development.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Each employee has an annual budget to allocate to professional development opportunities. Employees are encouraged to take a workshop, attend a webinar, join associations, and do anything else that will help them grow in their careers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;And more!&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;We offer flexible time off, life insurance, LTD, a robust employee assistance program, and more!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;At CG Life, we recognize that attracting the best talent is key to our strategy and success as a company

